## Windows CMD Basic Commands Cheat Sheet (Junior Level / Same as Linux basics)

### 1. Navigation & Listing
dir                     # List files and folders in current directory (Linux: ls)
dir /a                  # Include hidden files and system files (Linux: ls -la)
dir /a:h                # Only hidden files
dir /s                  # Recursive – current + all subfolders mein list (Linux: ls -R)
dir /p                  # Page by page (pause kar ke dekhne ke liye)
dir /b                  # Bare format – sirf naam, no extra details
cd                      # Current directory ka path dikhao (Linux: pwd) – agar argument nahi diya
cd <path>               # Change directory (Linux: cd <path>)
cd ..                   # Ek folder peeche jaao (Linux: cd ..)
cd \                    # Root drive (jaise C:\) pe jaao
cd ~                    # Nahi chalta Windows CMD mein (Linux mein home hota hai)
pushd <path>            # Folder change + stack pe save (baad mein popd se wapas)
popd                    # Pehle wale folder pe wapas

### 2. File Contents Display
type <file.txt>         # File ka content screen pe dikhao (Linux: cat <file>)
more <file.txt>         # Page by page dekhne ke liye (Linux: more / less)
type file.txt | more    # Same as above

### 3. Clear Screen
cls                     # Screen clear kar do (Linux: clear ya Ctrl+L)

### 4. Basic File/Folder Operations (Bonus – common ones)
copy file.txt d:\backup\   # File copy (Linux: cp)
xcopy folder1 d:\backup /s /e  # Folder copy recursive (Linux: cp -r)
move file.txt d:\new\      # Move / rename (Linux: mv)
del file.txt               # Delete file (Linux: rm)
del /s /q folder\*.*       # Folder ke andar sab delete (careful!)
mkdir newfolder            # Naya folder banao (Linux: mkdir)
rmdir folder               # Empty folder delete (Linux: rmdir)
rmdir /s /q folder         # Folder + andar sab delete (Linux: rm -r -f)

### 5. Current Location & System Info
cd                         # Current path dikhao (Linux: pwd)
chdir                      # Same as cd (without argument)
ver                        # Windows version dikhao
systeminfo                 # Full system info (RAM, OS, etc.)
time                       # Time dekho / set karo
date                       # Date dekho / set karo
